article_title: Small Earthquake Reported In Garfield County - News9.com - Oklahoma City, OK - News, Weather, Video and Sports
article_text:
A small earthquake shook residents awake early Sunday morning in Garfield County.

A 3.0 magnitude quake struck at just before 5:00 a.m. Its epicenter was located 11 miles southeast of Helena, 13 miles west of Enid, and 53 miles northwest of Guthrie.

It was about a mile deep.

No injuries or damages have been reported at this time.
